place.name: FULMODESTON
place.gazetteerText: FULMODESTON-CUM-CROXTON, a parish in Walsingham district, Norfolk; 3 miles NE of Ryburgh r. station, and 4 E of Fakenham. Post town, Ryburgh, under Fakenham. Acres, 2, 333. Real property, £3, 282. Pop., 400. Houses, 87. The property is not much divided. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £460.* Patron, Corpus Christi College, Oxford. The church is ancient, but very good; and contains monuments of the Brownes and others. There is a chapel of ease at Croxton, also very good. Charities, inclusive of a fuel allotment, £69. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
